250 g Ground Beef
1 tbsp Jerk Spice Blend
1 tbsp Cumin-Turmeric Spice Blend
¾ cup Jasmine Rice
113 g Mirepoix
56 g Green Peas
7 g Cilantro
1 unit Beef Broth Concentrate
½ tsp Salt*
¼ tsp Pepper*
1 tbsp Butter*
½ tbsp Sugar*
1 tbsp Garlic Puree
2 unit Green Onion
½ tbsp Oil*

Before starting, wash and dry all produce.

Heat a medium pot over medium-high heat. When hot, add 1/2 tbsp oil (dbl for 4 ppl), then Cumin-Turmeric Spice Blend. Cook, stirring often, unti fragrant, 2-3 min. Add rice, peas, 1 1/4 cups water and 1/4 tsp salt (dbl both for 4 ppl) and bring to a boil over high heat. Reduce heat to low. Cover and cook, until rice is tender and liquid is absorbed, 12-14 min.

While rice cooks, heat a large non-stick pan over medium-high heat. When hot, add the beef. Cook, breaking up beef into smaller pieces, until no pink remains, 4-5 min.\*\* Add Jerk Spice Blend and 1/2 tbsp sugar (dbl for 4 ppl) and cook, stirring often, until fragrant, 2-3 min. Season with salt and pepper.

Add garlic puree and mirepoix to the pan. Cook, stirring often, until fragrant and mirepoix is slightly softened, 2-3 min. Add broth concentrate and 1 cup water (dbl for 4 ppl). Reduce heat to medium and cook until beef sauce is slightly reduced 2-3 min.

While the beef sauce is reducing, finely chop cilantro. Thinly slice green onions.

Fluff rice with a fork. Stir 1 tbsp butter (dbl for 4 ppl) into beef sauce. Divide rice between bowls. Top with beef sauce. Sprinkle cilantro and green onions over top.